cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IT

This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of overparameterization, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization, and thus cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions experiments on image classification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper's focus on optimization and acceleration also suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
